{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"o1lmi4rif7tlnkle0ckp2gp","title":"Systemd","desc":"","updated":1661420028102,"created":1661361194018,"custom":{},"fname":"linux.service.systemd","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"031e25d57aff617e42bca21018859b4f","links":[],"anchors":{"systemd-system-and-service-manager":{"type":"header","text":"Systemd system and service manager","value":"systemd-system-and-service-manager","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1},"install":{"type":"header","text":"Install","value":"install","line":13,"column":0,"depth":2},"setup-a-service":{"type":"header","text":"Setup a service","value":"setup-a-service","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2},"other-commands":{"type":"header","text":"Other commands","value":"other-commands","line":45,"column":0,"depth":2},"read-logs":{"type":"header","text":"Read logs","value":"read-logs","line":52,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"tdn31rcl0l8818om4d2uj9s","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"systemd\">Systemd<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#systemd\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"systemd-system-and-service-manager\">Systemd system and service manager<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#systemd-system-and-service-manager\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://wiki.debian.org/systemd\">https://wiki.debian.org/systemd</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.computernetworkingnotes.com/linux-tutorials/systemd-unit-configuration-files-explained.html\">https://www.computernetworkingnotes.com/linux-tutorials/systemd-unit-configuration-files-explained.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"install\">Install<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#install\"></a></h2>\n<pre><code>sudo apt update\nsudo apt install systemd\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"setup-a-service\">Setup a service<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#setup-a-service\"></a></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.shubhamdipt.com/blog/how-to-create-a-systemd-service-in-linux/\">https://www.shubhamdipt.com/blog/how-to-create-a-systemd-service-in-linux/</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>cd <code>/etc/systemd/system</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>create a config file <code>&#x3C;service-name>.service</code></p>\n<pre><code>[Unit]\nDescription=&#x3C;description about this service>\n\n[Service]\nUser=&#x3C;user e.g. root>\nWorkingDirectory=&#x3C;directory_of_script e.g. /root>\nExecStart=&#x3C;script which needs to be executed>\nRestart=always\nStandardError=journal\nStandardOutput=journal\nStandardInput=null\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>reload all service <code>sudo systemctl daemon-reload</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>start your service <code>sudo systemctl start &#x3C;service-name>.service</code></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"other-commands\">Other commands<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#other-commands\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Stop a service (not on every boot): <code>sudo systemctl stop &#x3C;service-name>.service</code></li>\n<li>Check status <code>sudo systemctl status &#x3C;service-name>.service</code></li>\n<li>Enable every boot <code>sudo systemctl enable &#x3C;service-name>.service</code></li>\n<li>Disable every boot <code>sudo systemctl disable &#x3C;service-name>.service</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"read-logs\">Read logs<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#read-logs\"></a></h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/225401/how-to-see-full-log-from-systemctl-status-service\">https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/225401/how-to-see-full-log-from-systemctl-status-service</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><code>journalctl -u &#x3C;service-name>.service\n</code></pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Must add to the config \n<pre><code>StandardError=journal\nStandardOutput=journal\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"xfkxbponh0sohobo6pual15","title":"Root",